I haven’t posted in a minute but one thing I would like to say is to make sure to truly value the people you have in your life. Tomorrow isn’t promised so make sure to cherish every moment you have with those people or that person . Don’t spend it consistently fighting because you never know if that would be your last time speaking with them. 

ON A BRIGHTER NOTE  HAPPY 27th BDAY BABE!!!! 
I’m proud of you Ash. Not just in your accomplishments but I’m proud of your fighting spirit. You never give up when things are hard and you always remember to pray to the Lord even when things are flowing smoothly.  You’ve played a huge role in how I view marriage and life in general . You keep me on my toes and I know if I ever need to hear the truth you won’t spare me 😂😂😂. You respect my leadership and everyone around you and for that you will forever be loved and cherished. Happy Bday Partner 😘😘😘😘
I think I’m going to get this hung up somewhere 😈
May we forever maintain our youth 🦾⚔️🖤🐺
Peace and prosperity 🦾⚔️🐺🖤
We finna be some sexy 40 year olds 😜

Let each day above dirt be a blessing . 

Lifestyle advice: Remember to pray even when you dont feel like it or when you think God doesn’t hear you. Live each day like it could potentially be your last. Don’t get so caught up on what happened previously that you forget to move forward. Remember to exercise and eat nutritious food because your longevity requires it. Remember to be kind because when you bless others God will always bless you with peace. Remember that you’re human and will make mistakes but you are not you’re mistakes. Know when to be quiet and also know when to speak. Know when to instruct and know when to ask for help. Remember that you can’t control what goes on outside but you can control the peace that resides within the walls of your home.
Idk who needs to hear this but you gotta be your biggest cheerleader!! Not because of the lack of support but because you simply gotta love what you do in spite of the outcome. 🦾🐺🖤⚔️

You may not think I understand but trust me we all have a story to tell . The first vid of me was a man battling with hypertension, over weight,stress , raised liver enzymes, self doubt, lack of confidence and self Iove. People ask me all the time “Sean why did you spend so much time from social media? I took time away because I needed to fix my foundation within my life. I needed time alone between me and my Heavenly Father to truly work on me, while I went through a spiritual cleanse . People see the smiles and pics but they don’t see the hidden battles that you face . To end this on a good note , Christ has been good to me even when I walk away from Him and for that I’ll always be thankful. I no longer have those health issues, marriage life has improved, mental health and mental clarity is sharp and I’ve missed you all🦾🐺⚔️🖤

Just another day in the lab. How you start your morning sets the tone for your day. 🦾🐺⚔️🖤

After reading this book I’ve come to the conclusion that marriage , relationships and friendships are one in the same.  All three consist of communication and unfortunately in this world most people lack communication and will swear up and down they’re the best communicator in the world. This book was written for couples where it explains how the mind of man works and how the mind of woman works and why there’s so much confusion at times when trying to get your point across and why it may seem like you’re speaking another language when talking to a man or woman. You literally are speaking another language and if you’re talking to someone who’s not aware of the difference in language your plight will fall on deaf ears . The same thing for friendships , if you can’t communicate with your friends when they’ve taken you for granted then those aren’t your friends, if you have a supervisor whose ego driven no matter how much facts you lay at their feet to make the workplace a smoother environment their pride will be the downfall of the company

In order to get better you’re going to have to developed a healthy relationship with pain. In this case I’m not talking about a life threatening pain but growing pains that are meant to help us along our developmental process and lifelong journey . The things you strongly desire whether it’s a nice physique, money to provide for your family ,even your spiritual journey requires you to face some pain in order to grow. Don’t try to avoid but embrace it 🦾⚔️🐺🖤
